# GENERAL_MATRIX
Problem solved using the programing language PORTUGOL, through visualg. Follow the instructions of the problem:

Read a square matrix (n order), containing real numbers. Then, do the following:

a) Calculate and print on the screen the sum of all positive numbers of the matrix
b) Read the line index and, then, print on the screen all the elements that belongs to this line
c) Read the index of a column and, then, print on the screen all of the elements of this column.
d) Print on the screen all of the main diagonal elements
e) Change the matrix, squaring all of its the negative numbers.
Then, print on the screen the matrix that has been changed.
